OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F443A1758392996
OL,3,CNew Troubles legacy framework founded
OL,4,Con 'reciprocal cooperation'
OL,6,F"It would be easy to hold out for the
OL,7,Fperfect, to inevitably fail, and then
OL,8,Fto stand criticising on the sidelines;
OL,9,Fa comfortable hurler on the ditch," he
OL,10,Fis expected to say.
OL,12,F"That would be a fundamental mistake;
OL,13,Fone that could not later be rectified."
OL,15,FMr Harris will urge victims and
OL,16,Fsurvivors to consider supporting the
OL,17,Fproposals.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@cO]tD@AOUuD@gO]
